{{Refimprove|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox magazine | logo = | logo_size = | image_file = | image_size = <!-- (defaults to user thumbnail size if no size is stated) --> | image_alt = | image_caption = | editor = | editor_title = | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = [[Pulp magazine]] | frequency = Monthly | circulation = | publisher = | founder = [[Leo Margulies]] | founded = 1931 | firstdate = | finaldate = 1943 | finalnumber = | company = | country = [[United States]] | based = | language = English | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | issn = | oclc = }}
'''''Thrilling Adventures''''' was a monthly American [[pulp magazine]] published from 1931 to 1943.<ref name=ah>Doug Ellis, John Locke, John Gunnison, ''The Adventure House Guide to the Pulps''. Adventure House, 2000, {{ISBN|1886937451}} (p. 270).</ref>
==History== ''Thrilling Adventures'' was created in 1931 by editor [[Leo Margulies]]<ref name=pfest>{{cite news|title=Leo Margulies at 115!|url=http://www.pulpfest.com/2015/06/leo-margulies-at-115/|accessdate=13 December 2015|work=Pulpfest|date=June 2015}}</ref> and was patterned after the pulp [[Adventure (magazine)|''Adventure'']]. It was one of 16 pulps that Margulies founded that incorporated the adjective "Thrilling" in the title. (The company that published the ''Thrilling'' titles eventually changed its name to [[Thrilling Publications]].)<ref name=pfest/> The first edition of ''Thrilling Adventures'' was published in December 1931.
''Thrilling Adventures'' published fictional stories, mostly of the adventure and sports genres.<ref>{{cite book|author=John Dinan|title=Sports in the Pulp Magazines|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7LvwCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA55|accessdate=13 December 2015|date=1 September 1998|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-1-4766-0767-2|page=55}}</ref> It continued as a monthly until 1943, when it was reduced to a bimonthly, and the final issue was the November 1943 edition.<ref name="ah"/> A total of 139 issues were published during its existence.<ref>{{cite web|title=Thrilling Adventures|url=http://www.pulpmags.org/thrilling_page.html|work=The Pulp Magazines Project|accessdate=4 September 2016}}</ref>
